WEAPONS

Weapons are gear you wield to fight in melee or at range. Wielding is
separate from wearing armor: wear protects you, wield lets you attack.

CHECKING YOUR GEAR
  eq                          shows what you have wielded and worn
                               (also: equipment, worn)

MELEE WEAPONS
  wield <weapon> in <limb>              wield a weapon to attack with it
  wield <weapon> in <limb> and <limb>   for two handed weapons
  unwield <weapon>                      put a weapon away
  unwield all                           put away everything wielded

  Melee weapons fall into a few types, such as blade, blunt, knife, and
  two handed. How good you are with each depends on your OCC's starting
  skills and W.P. (Weapon Proficiency) picks from character generation,
  not a fixed class list.

RANGED WEAPONS
  fire <target>                 attack with a wielded ranged weapon
  fire <weapon> at <target>
  shoot <target>                 same as fire
  reload <weapon> [with <ammo>]  load ammo or an e-clip into a weapon
  unload <weapon>                remove the current ammo or clip

  Ranged weapons need ammo, such as an e-clip, loaded before they can
  fire. See reload and unload for the full syntax.

SEE ALSO: wield, unwield, wear, eq, fire, shoot, reload, unload
